			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Chief Technology Officer (CTO)</strong><br />
Rocket Internet - Lazada South East Asia</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>About Rocket Internet</strong><br />
Rocket Internet is the leading Internet start-up incubator in Europe and beyond. Over the past years we have launched some of the most respected Internet companies globally. Some of the best-known ventures include Groupon, Lazada, Zalora, eDarling, Wimdu, Foodpanda and Pricepanda</p>
<p>
<strong>About Lazada</strong><br />
Lazada &ndash; the leading online department store in South East Asia &ndash; launched in late March and is headquartered in Singapore. Lazada is already fully operational in 5 countries (Malaysia, Vietnam, Indonesia, Thailand, Philippines) and is growing at an impressive speed</p>
<p>
Become a member of our great international team and join a group of young and motivated entrepreneurs with various backgrounds (e.g. McKinsey, BCG, Goldman, Google, Oracle). This is a unique opportunity to gain valuable and challenging experience at a rapidly expanding start-up company. You will be able to use your initiative and creativity to support our expansion</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Job Description</strong></p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Provide technical leadership in system design, high-performance, and scalable architectures</li>
<li>
Implement and improve software development processes such as Agile, Scrum, XP, Kanban along with strong robust coordination processes related to software deployments and testing</li>
<li>
Build, develop and manage a large team of developers, testers and system administration experts</li>
<li>
Mentor younger software enginers and development managers into rock star software development experts</li>
<li>
You will be in charge of code quality and architecture and engineering talent development</li>
<li>
You will manage projects, timelines and releases and push the envelop in talent productivity and software effectiveness</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We Offer:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Opportunity to work in a fast-moving, challenging but informal work environment with major international projects</li>
<li>
Ability to impact millions of users on the largest e-commerce website in Southeast Asia</li>
<li>
As CTO, you will have a key role in building large and successful e-commerce businesses</li>
<li>
Highly competitive compensation</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Your skills:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You love good software development &ndash; simplicity, common sense, elegant code</li>
<li>
You are experienced at architecting large software systems &ndash; you know scalability, security, data access, parallel processing, performance profiling, and multiple system communications</li>
<li>
You have used modern web frameworks &ndash; preferably in PHP such as Zend</li>
<li>
You are a fast thinker, hands on manager and strong communicator; you think and act like an entrepreneur</li>
<li>
You know agile development, quality assurance, and software release processes and tools. Not just from books. You know how to do fast release cycles without compromising on quality</li>
<li>
You speak English fluently</li>
<li>
You have an outstanding university degree in a technical subject and several years&rsquo; experience in a lead architect, VP of Engineering, or CTO position</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You can have experience with large scale operational eCommerce websites</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
